  "difficultyLevel": 3,
  "lyrics": "save tonight Got up flight in the morning, baby just save\ntonight\neagle eyed cherry, on my radio Telling us to love the moment, to stay here\nEven though tomorrow brings us problems And there'll be nothing good for you to save\nfor me, but save tonight\nGot this glass of wine, baby, let's share it tonight\nDon't worry about the fight, save tonight\nWhen you look in my eyes, save the fight When you ask yourself why, save tonight\nFor we could be there, save tonight, save tonight, save all of our nights\nIt's one more drink, one more down You negative perception of me, takes it to\nthe crown Now you just wanna shoot me down\nOn my knees, as far as I had to fall When believing my choices were right\nOh, come on, baby, do me one last thing And save tonight\nMake it right, baby, save tonight Oh, make it right for me, and save tonight\nIt might be the last that we see this light Save our night, save our night\nCause at the end of it all, the night is dawn I know you'll see me there, asking you to\ncarry on, save tonight",
